 Given my risk-averse nature and preference for certainty, I would choose a strategy that maximizes the likelihood of earning a consistent payout, even if it is not the highest possible amount per round. In this case, choosing B ensures a minimum payout of 12$ per round.

However, considering that the game has 75 rounds, and the probability of both players consistently picking the same choice (R or B) in each round is very low, it's more likely that one player will deviate from their initial choice at some point to maximize their potential earnings. If I stick with B, I can ensure a minimum payout while also potentially gaining an advantage if my opponent decides to switch strategies.

In this situation, the strategy of always picking B seems to be the most secure and consistent one for me as a risk-averse player, although it may not maximize potential earnings in every round. {B}
